      "side": 1,
      "message": "Reports are only ever generated by the Database in response to the various queries that are on it:\n\n\"\"\"\nAll Report objects that are returned by this class are logically const.\nThey are snapshots of the database at the time the query was run, and the\ndata returned is liable to change after the query is executed.\n\"\"\"\n\nSo nothing should be serializing Report objects; the only valid bit to persist from a Report is the UUID.\n\nReports are primarily used by clients for displaying information about crashes in a UI (e.g. chrome://crashes). The database can simply fill in the field as another type of metadata when creating the Report objects.",
